board and she said you're going

00:11:57.070 --> 00:11:58.380
to put strings in those
white school,

00:11:58.380 --> 00:11:59.680
you're going to put
them in my school!

00:11:59.680 --> 00:12:00.980
&gt;&gt; Nick Brown: Wow.

00:12:00.980 --> 00:12:03.960
&gt;&gt; Thomas Wilkins: And they
just could not say no to her.

00:12:03.960 --> 00:12:06.090
And had she not done that,

00:12:06.090 --> 00:12:07.440
that violin wouldn't
have been there for me.

00:12:07.440 --> 00:12:08.740
&gt;&gt; Nick Brown: That's amazing.

00:12:08.740 --> 00:12:10.040
&gt;&gt; Thomas Wilkins: Yes!

00:12:10.040 --> 00:12:12.150
So that was fourth grade and then
we could switch in fifth grade

00:12:12.150 --> 00:12:15.850
and I switched to cello, that sort
of became my principle instrument.

00:12:15.850 --> 00:12:19.870
And then in seventh grade, so I
